content:
Configure Aura Guest User Access

Create a Visualforce page for your Aura Service Catalog Site so guest users have access to view and request catalog items.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions with the Customer Service Catalog add-on license.
Service Catalog site requires Service Catalog User permission set and a Channel Account or Partner Community license.
To set up Service Catalog site guest users: 
Permissions associated with the Service Catalog Site Builder
Create and Set Up Experiences
Manage Profiles and Permission Sets

This article applies to: Aura Experience Sites
Does not apply to: LWR Experience sites, Salesforce sites, and externally built sites

Before you begin, ensure youâ€™ve set up guest users for Service Catalog. See Set Up Service Catalog Guest Users.

Step I: Create a Visualforce Page

Use a Visualforce page to present your catalog items to guest users in your Service Catalog site.
From Setup, enter and select Visualforce Pages
Click New
For the Label field, enter a name
Enable Available for Lightning Experience, Experience Builder sites, and the mobile app
Enter this code:
<apex:page showHeader="false" sidebar="false">
  <apex:includeLightning />
  <div id="item" />
    <script>
        $Lightning.use("runtime_service_servicecatalog:serviceCatalogLightningOut", function() {
          $Lightning.createComponent("runtime_service_servicecatalog:catalogItem",
              {itemApiName: 'item_1708593530216_ItemFlow1'},
              "item",
              function(cmp) {
                console.log("Item runner created");
                // do some stuff
              }
          );
        });
    </script>
</apex:page>

Save your work.

Step II: Set Your Site Access Setting

Grant your guest users access to the Visualforce page.
From Experience Workspaces, enable Let guest users view asset files, library files, and CMS content available to the site.
From Experience Builder, select Enabled Visualforce Page Access quick action
Add Visualforce page you created
Save your work.

Step III: Add the Visualforce Page to the Site

Connect the Visualforce Page to your Service Catalog site.
From Experience Builder, place the Visualforce Page component in the right column of the page
Publish your changes.
title: Configure Aura Guest User Access in Service Cloud
